00:14:42.778 --> 00:14:46.578
"Etzioni would likely advocate for a go slow approach

243
00:14:46.878 --> 00:14:50.558
that rigorously validates these tests in trials, focusing

244
00:14:50.618 --> 00:14:54.558
on minimizing patient harm and

245
00:14:54.618 --> 00:14:58.358
ensuring the technological advances

246
00:14:58.598 --> 00:15:02.478
benefit the community rather than thus being driven by

247
00:15:02.538 --> 00:15:03.318
commercial hype."

248
00:15:05.238 --> 00:15:06.657
I would agree with much of that.

249
00:15:06.878 --> 00:15:07.398
Scary.

250
00:15:07.938 --> 00:15:11.138
But I strongly disagree with the emphasis on go slow.

251
00:15:11.978 --> 00:15:15.578
To the contrary, we must search for a faster approach that still

252
00:15:15.618 --> 00:15:19.398
ensures rigorous evaluation. The focus should be on maximizing

