1035
01:00:46.098 --> 01:00:49.998
This is not unique to MCED. So the emphasis on

1036
01:00:50.058 --> 01:00:50.998
that, I think, is

1037
01:00:51.878 --> 01:00:53.618
probably a little bit overblown.

1038
01:00:55.118 --> 01:00:57.238
False negatives and reassurance.

1039
01:00:57.548 --> 01:01:01.458
So the big harm here is happily living

1040
01:01:01.558 --> 01:01:04.398
thinking you don't have cancer even though you might.

1041
01:01:05.138 --> 01:01:08.078
That's really only harmful if you skip screenings.

1042
01:01:08.318 --> 01:01:10.798
That's the risk. Otherwise,

1043
01:01:11.838 --> 01:01:15.178
having a screening test that yields a negative result

1044
01:01:15.798 --> 01:01:19.598
even though eventually you get a cancer, is not really a meaningful harm

